**The set of natural numbers**

0 < 1 < 2 < 3 < ...

ordered set
discrete set

The set of all natural numbers is CLOSED UNDER addition and multiplication.

0 is the neutral element of addition
n + 0 = n for all n ∈ ℕ

1 is the neutral element of multiplication
n · 1 = n for all n ∈ ℕ

addition: term + term = sum
multiplication: factor × factor = product
factorization

Multiplication is repeated addition
5 × 3 = 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3

Powers are repeated multiplications
5³ = 5 × 5 × 5

Factorization ( Video 10 )

Precedence rule: multiplication has higher precedence than addition
4 × 2 + 5 = 8 + 5

2 + 2 + 2 + 2 + 5

